paper_metadata.title: MAIN TEXT
paper_metadata.extraction_summary: Extracted genetic variant information for BRCA2, including penetrance data.

patients.demographics: Korean ethnicity, including one male patient
patients.phenotype: hormone receptor-positive breast cancer accounted for 75% of patients with pathogenic gBRCA2 mutations

functional_data.summary: The most common variants were Arg2494Ter (7 of 28, 25.0%) and Lys467Ter (4 of 28, 14.3%).

variants.additional_notes: The only male patient had a nonsense mutation in gBRCA2 (p.Ile332PhefsTer17).
key_quotes: Among gBRCA2 mutations, Arg2494Ter (7 of 28, 25.0%) and Lys467Ter (4 of 28, 14.3%) were the most common.

extraction_metadata.notes: All relevant data for BRCA2 variants were extracted successfully.
